  "instructions": [
    "Heat the olive oil in the bottom of a tagine or Dutch oven over medium-high heat.",
    "Add the chopped onion and cook until browned, about 5 minutes.",
    "Add the minced garlic and grated ginger and cook for 1 minute.",
    "Add the cumin, coriander, paprika, salt, and black pepper and cook for 1 minute.",
    "Add the chicken and cook until browned on all sides, about 5 minutes.",
    "Add the gochujang and cook for 1 minute.",
    "Stir in the chopped fresh parsley and cook for 1 minute.",
    "Transfer the tagine to the oven and cook at 425°F for 25-30 minutes, or until the chicken is cooked through and the sauce is thick and caramelized.",
    "Meanwhile, heat a small amount of oil in a pan over medium-high heat and fry the khao khua until crispy, breaking it up with a spoon as it cooks.",
    "Sprinkle the fried khao khua over the top of the tagine and serve hot."
  ],
